title: Why don’t we trust the experts? (2016)

People who publish open-source projects, what makes you confident to do that?
text:
Writing some patchy code for some personal project is one thing. But publishing well structured and documented code to the world as an usable package is another thing.

People who do that on a regular basis, what made you capable or confident enough that you can trust your own code to run on other people's machines without the fear of failure?

Was it some specific topic in CS or something that gave you that confidence boost? e.g: some people say I gained confidence after taking an OS course or a Compilers course. Is it like that or is it by reading other people's code?
